headline: WMT Q1 Earnings Call: Margin Expansion Offsets Revenue Miss as Walmart Navigates Tariff Headwinds
summary: Retail behemoth Walmart (NYSE:WMT) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025 as sales rose 2.5% year on year to $165.6 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $0.61 per share was 5.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
